# Plans

> Phased implementation roadmap for AutoForge. Each plan references Goals (G), Architecture (A), and Designs (D) for traceability.


## P1: Relay Run Completion Notification in Chat

**Status:** In Progress (Backend complete, frontend pending)
**Objective:** G23 (Automatic Relay Mode), G18 (Wiki module)
**Estimated Duration:** 4 sprints
**Owner:** Documenter (backend), Frontend Team (UI)

**Overview:**
Implement a notification system that alerts the user in the chat where a Relay Run was initiated when the run completes. If the run produced a Report, include a link to view it.

**Phase Breakdown:**

| Phase | Task | Owner | Duration | Dependencies | Status | Detail |
|---|---|---|---|---|---|---|
| P1.1 | Data model changes — `generated_report` field | Core | 1 day | D3 | Done | Add `generated_report: Option<ReportReference>` to `HandoffDocument` per D3 §Schema. Define `ReportReference` struct with `report_id`, `report_title`, `wiki_slug`. File: `backend/src/relay/handoff.rs`. Deliverable: struct serializes to JSON. |
| P1.2 | Chat-Relay Association (future) | Core | 1 day | — | Pending | Add `originating_chat_session: Option<String>` to `RunMetadata` per A13 §Metadata. This enables routing notifications to the correct chat session instead of broadcasting. File: `backend/src/relay/mod.rs`. Deliverable: spawn API accepts optional `chat_session_id`. |
| P2.1 | Completion notification builder | Core | 2 days | P1.1 | Done | Implement `build_completion_notification()` in `backend/src/relay/driver.rs` per D3 §Notification. Extract run metadata (title, status, summary), check for `generated_report` in last handoff, build `RelayCompleteNotification` event. Use `relay::title::generate_title()`. Deliverable: notification JSON includes all fields. |
| P2.2 | Event emission on run completion | Core | 1 day | P2.1 | Done | Modify `drive_run()` to: (1) build completion notification on finish, (2) persist to `RunEntry.events`, (3) broadcast via SSE with type `relay_complete_notification`, (4) maintain backward compatibility with legacy `run_completed` event per D3 §Events. Deliverable: SSE client receives event. |
| P3.2 | Report generation integration | Documenter | 2 days | P2.2 | Partial | Documenter agent must populate `handoff.generated_report = Some(ReportReference { ... })` when creating reports per D3 §Report Link. File: `backend/src/relay/documenter.rs`. Deliverable: completed runs with documenter step include report link. |
| P4.1 | Frontend notification bubble | UI | 2 days | P2.2 | Pending | Handle `relay_complete` SSE event in `ChatsView.vue` per D17 §Notification. Render notification bubble with distinct styling (success/failure icons). Show "View Report" button when `report_link` present. Navigate to `/wiki/{slug}` or `/specs/reports?report_id={id}`. Deliverable: bubble appears on completion. |

**Risk:** Notification arrives before session is updated; old relay references accumulate in sessions; report generation fails but run completes.
**Mitigation:** Events persisted in `RunEntry.events` for replay; add cleanup job for runs older than 24h; gracefully handle missing `report_slug`, show notification without link.

**Depends on:** G23, G18, D5, D3, A8

**Related Specs:** G23 (Automatic Relay Mode), G18 (Wiki module), D5 (Relay Run Titles), A8 (Chat-First Gate Approval)

