## P1 Agents Relay — Foundation
**Status:** done
**Depends on:** G1, G2, G3, D1, D3

| Phase | Task | Owner | Duration | Dependencies | Status | Detail |
|---|---|---|---|---|---|---|
| P1.1 | Soul + Profession data model and registry | Tooling | 3 days | D1 | Done | Define `AgentInstance` struct with `soul_id`, `profession_id`, `model_config` per D1 §Data Model. Build `ProfessionRegistry` singleton with `register()` / `get()` / `list()` APIs. New file: `backend/src/relay/profession.rs`. Deliverable: registry unit tests pass for all operations. |
| P1.2 | Built-in professions | Tooling | 2 days | P1.1 | Done | Create `Profession` enum with `Intaker`, `Planner`, `Architect`, `Coder`, `Tester`, `Reviewer` variants per D1 §Profession Registry. Define `owned_sections`, `handoff_to`, and `allowed_tools` for each profession. Deliverable: all 6 professions registered and enumerable via API. |
| P1.3 | Default Soul configs in `.autoforge/souls/` | Tooling | 2 days | P1.1 | Done | Create `.autoforge/souls/` directory structure with default soul markdown files per D1 §Soul Rendering. Implement `SoulRenderer` that reads `.md` files and injects profession context (name, role, owned_sections). Deliverable: soul files loadable at runtime with correct profession substitution. |
| P1.4 | ModelConfig with provider abstraction and fallback chain | Tooling | 2 days | P1.1 | Done | Define `ModelConfig` struct with `provider`, `model_name`, `api_key_ref`, `max_tokens`, `temperature` per D1 §Provider Abstraction. Implement provider enum: `OpenAI`, `Anthropic`, `Local`. Support fallback chain: primary → secondary → local. File: `backend/src/forge/ai.rs`. Deliverable: config serializes to/from TOML correctly. |
| P1.5 | Refactor existing Forge into reusable `AgentTurn` engine | Tooling | 3 days | P1.2 | Done | Extract chat loop logic from `forge/mod.rs` into reusable `AgentTurn` struct per D1 §Agent Turn. `AgentTurn` takes `AgentInstance` + message history, returns streaming response with token usage. Deliverable: existing chat functionality unchanged; `AgentTurn` usable by Relay pipeline without chat UI dependencies. |
| P1.6 | HandoffDocument schema and generation | Tooling | 3 days | D3 | Done | Define `HandoffDocument` struct with `from_profession`, `to_profession`, `summary`, `specs_touched`, `files_changed` per D3 §Schema. Implement JSON serialization with `skip_serializing_if` for optional fields. File: `backend/src/relay/handoff.rs`. Deliverable: document round-trips through JSON without data loss. |
| P1.7 | Context scoping: filter specs by profession | Tooling | 2 days | P1.6 | Done | Implement `SpecFilter` that takes a `Profession` and returns only relevant spec sections per D3 §Context Scoping. Use `owned_sections` to determine relevance: Architect sees Architecture+Designs; Coder sees Designs+Plans; Tester sees Plans+Tests. Deliverable: filtered context < 50% of full spec size. |
| P1.8 | Handoff compression (cheap model or rule-based) | Tooling | 2 days | P1.6 | Done | Implement `HandoffCompressor` trait with two implementations: `CheapModelCompressor` (uses cheap LLM to summarize) and `RuleBasedCompressor` (heuristic truncation of message history) per D3 §Compression. Deliverable: compressed handoff < 4k tokens; unit tests for both strategies with realistic handoffs. |
| P1.9 | Unit tests for AgentInstance and Handoff generation | Tooling | 2 days | P1.5, P1.6 | Done | Write integration tests for `AgentInstance::run_turn()`, `HandoffDocument::generate()`, and `ProfessionRegistry` lookups per D1 §Testing. Test file: `backend/tests/relay_agent_tests.rs`. Mock LLM provider for deterministic tests. Deliverable: >80% coverage on relay core types. |



