## P2 Agents Relay — Flow Engine
**Status:** done
**Depends on:** G2, G6, D2, P1

| Phase | Task | Owner | Duration | Dependencies | Status | Detail |
|---|---|---|---|---|---|---|
| P2.1 | FlowSpec parser (AutoDown-based DSL) | Tooling | 3 days | D2 | Done | Implement AutoDown-based DSL parser for flow definitions per D2 §FlowSpec DSL. Parse `step`, `gate`, `branch`, `loop` directives into `FlowSpec` AST. Support comments and nested blocks. File: `backend/src/relay/flow.rs`. Deliverable: all example flows in `designs/` parse without error. |
| P2.2 | PipelineEngine state machine | Tooling | 3 days | D2 | Done | Build `PipelineEngine` with states: `Idle`, `Running`, `Paused`, `Completed`, `Failed` per D2 §State Machine. Implement `step()` method that advances one phase with transition validation. File: `backend/src/relay/pipeline.rs`. Deliverable: all state transitions tested via mock flows. |
| P2.3 | Step execution: spawn agent, run turn, collect result | Tooling | 2 days | P1.5, P2.2 | Done | Implement `execute_step()` that spawns an `AgentInstance`, runs `AgentTurn`, and collects result into `StepResult` per D2 §Step Execution. Wire `AgentInstance` into pipeline with context injection. Deliverable: single-step flow runs end-to-end with real LLM. |
| P2.4 | Flow branching: Intaker → DIRECT vs full pipeline | Tooling | 2 days | P2.2 | Done | Implement `BranchEvaluator` that routes flow based on gate outcome: `DIRECT` (skip to Coder) vs full pipeline per D2 §Branching. Use `Intaker` classification result to determine branch. Deliverable: both branches tested with mock gates; branch choice logged. |
| P2.5 | Flow looping: Coder ↔ Tester with max iteration bound | Tooling | 2 days | P2.2 | Done | Implement Coder↔Tester retry loop with `max_iterations` bound (default 3, max 5) per D2 §Looping. Track iteration count in `StepResult`. Exit early on success. Deliverable: loop terminates at bound; success exits early; infinite loop impossible. |
| P2.6 | Human gates: pause, notify, approve/reject/edit | Tooling | 3 days | D2 | Done | Implement gate pause mechanism: emit SSE `gate_reached`, wait for HTTP `approve`/`reject`/`edit` per D2 §Human Gates. Store gate state in `RunEntry` with timeout (default 24h). Deliverable: gate pauses flow; resume continues from same step; reject routes to redraft. |
| P2.7 | Gate rejection routing back to drafting profession | Tooling | 2 days | P2.6 | Done | On gate reject, route back to drafting profession with feedback injected per D2 §Rejection Routing. Inject rejection reason into next turn's system message. Track rejection count per step. Deliverable: reject→redraft→re-gate cycle works; max 3 rejections before escalation. |
| P2.8 | Deterministic orchestrator unit tests | Tooling | 2 days | P2.1-P2.7 | Done | Write unit tests for `PipelineEngine` with mock agents per D2 §Testing. Test all state transitions, branching, looping, gating. Use `tokio::test` for async tests. Deliverable: 100% state machine coverage; all edge cases documented. |



