## P3 Agents Relay — Checkpoint & Durability
**Status:** done
**Depends on:** G4, D4, P2

| Phase | Task | Owner | Duration | Dependencies | Status | Detail |
|---|---|---|---|---|---|---|
| P3.1 | Checkpoint data model and JSON serialization | Tooling | 2 days | D4 | Done | Define `Checkpoint` struct with `run_id`, `step_id`, `timestamp`, `agent_state`, `file_manifest`, `ledger_state` per D4 §Data Model. Implement JSON schema with serde. File: `backend/src/relay/checkpoint.rs`. Deliverable: schema validates against test fixtures. |
| P3.2 | File manifest capture (hash, size) | Tooling | 2 days | D4 | Done | Implement `FileManifest::capture()` that walks project directory, records `path`, `hash` (SHA-256), `size` per D4 §Manifest. Exclude `.git/`, `target/`, `node_modules/`, `.autoforge/`. Deliverable: manifest matches `find | sha256sum` output for tracked files. |
| P3.3 | Git integration: auto-commit or diff capture | Tooling | 2 days | D4 | Done | Add optional git integration: auto-commit at checkpoint with message `checkpoint: {run_id}@{step_id}` OR capture `git diff` per D4 §Git. Use `git2` crate. Configurable via `project.autoforge.git_strategy`. Deliverable: checkpoint creates commit OR stores diff; both paths tested. |
| P3.4 | Checkpoint save/load on disk | Tooling | 2 days | P3.1 | Done | Implement `CheckpointStore` with `save()` → `{project}/.autoforge/checkpoints/{run_id}/{step_id}.json` and `load()` per D4 §Storage. Atomic write (temp file + rename). Deliverable: save/load round-trip preserves all fields; corruption impossible. |
| P3.5 | Resume from checkpoint: restore files, ledger, state | Tooling | 3 days | P3.4 | Done | Implement `PipelineEngine::resume_from(checkpoint_id)` that restores files from manifest, ledger state, and pipeline position per D4 §Resume. Verify file hashes match before restore. Deliverable: resumed run continues from exact step; no data loss. |
| P3.6 | Rehydrate agent from checkpoint (no chat history) | Tooling | 2 days | P3.5 | Done | Restore agent message history and context from checkpoint WITHOUT full chat replay per D4 §Rehydration. Use compressed handoff as system message. Reconstruct `AgentInstance` from saved state. Deliverable: agent responds correctly after rehydration; no replay needed. |
| P3.7 | Rollback to previous checkpoint | Tooling | 2 days | P3.4 | Done | Implement `rollback(checkpoint_id)` that restores file manifest and resets pipeline state per D4 §Rollback. Warn if subsequent checkpoints exist. Deliverable: rollback restores files to checkpoint state; subsequent resume works from rolled-back state. |
| P3.8 | Fork run from checkpoint with different parameters | Tooling | 2 days | P3.7 | Done | Implement `fork(checkpoint_id, new_params)` that clones checkpoint into new `RunEntry` with modified parameters (e.g., different model, different flow) per D4 §Fork. New run ID generated. Deliverable: forked run starts from checkpoint with new config; original unchanged. |
| P3.9 | Crash recovery integration tests | Tooling | 2 days | P3.5-P3.8 | Done | Write tests that simulate crash mid-step: kill process during `AgentTurn`, verify checkpoint integrity on restart per D4 §Testing. Use `std::process::abort` in test helper. Deliverable: crash recovery works 100% of time in test suite. |



