## P4 Agents Relay — Token Budgeting & Analytics
**Status:** done
**Depends on:** G5, D5, P2

| Phase | Task | Owner | Duration | Dependencies | Status | Detail |
|---|---|---|---|---|---|---|
| P4.1 | TokenBudget and BudgetTracker data model | Tooling | 2 days | D5 | Done | Define `TokenBudget` struct with `limit`, `consumed`, `warn_threshold`, `compression_threshold` and `BudgetTracker` singleton per D5 §Data Model. Support per-run and per-profession budgets. File: `backend/src/relay/budget.rs`. Deliverable: budget arithmetic unit-tested. |
| P4.2 | Per-step and per-run token tracking | Tooling | 2 days | D5 | Done | Integrate token counting into `AgentTurn::run()`: count prompt + completion tokens per step, aggregate to run total per D5 §Tracking. Use provider-reported token counts when available; estimate via tiktoken when not. Deliverable: token count within 5% of provider billing. |
| P4.3 | Budget enforcement: warning, compression, hard-stop | Tooling | 2 days | P4.2 | Done | Implement three-tier enforcement per D5 §Enforcement: `warn` (SSE notification to user), `compress` (trigger handoff compression), `hard_stop` (terminate run with summary). Configurable thresholds (default: warn 50%, compress 75%, stop 100%). Deliverable: all three tiers tested with mock budgets. |
| P4.4 | Model escalation fallback on budget exceed | Tooling | 2 days | P4.3 | Done | On budget exceed, fallback to cheaper model tier per D5 §Fallback. Implement `ModelTier` enum: `cheap`, `mid`, `premium`. Auto-downgrade on compression trigger. Deliverable: fallback reduces cost by >30% in test scenarios. |
| P4.5 | Cost analytics API (per run, per profession, cumulative) | Tooling | 2 days | P4.2 | Done | Add REST endpoints: `GET /api/relay/runs/{id}/cost`, `GET /api/relay/analytics` per D5 §Analytics. Return per-run, per-profession, cumulative stats with time series. Deliverable: API returns correct JSON with all aggregations. |
| P4.6 | "Savings vs parallel" estimation heuristic | Tooling | 2 days | P4.5 | Done | Implement heuristic that estimates token savings from serial handoffs vs parallel multi-agent per D5 §Savings. Compare full history replay vs compressed handoff token count. Display in analytics. Deliverable: heuristic shows >3x savings for 6-profession flows. |
| P4.7 | Unit tests for budget enforcement | Tooling | 2 days | P4.3 | Done | Write tests for budget thresholds, compression triggers, and hard stops per D5 §Testing. Mock token counts to test exact boundary conditions. Deliverable: all edge cases covered (exactly at threshold, 1 token over, etc.). |



